  "umaru": [
    {
      "message": "docs: standardize prompts with detailed Chinese translations\n\n- Translate the answer generation prompt to Chinese with additional formatting and detailed requirements for JSON output.\n- Translate the question generation prompt to Chinese with clear constraints and rules for generating JSON-based questions.\n- Add a code review prompt with comprehensive principles for code quality, logging, dependencies, performance, security, and decision-making criteria.\n\nSigned-off-by: umaru <15875339926@139.com>",
      "date": "2025-09-17T08:47:10Z"
    },
    {
      "message": "style: improve code readability and API consistency\n\n- Remove an unnecessary line break for improved formatting in the `chunk_type` description.\n\nSigned-off-by: umaru <15875339926@139.com>",
      "date": "2025-09-17T06:17:04Z"
    },
    {
      "message": "chore: relax documentation requirements for public interfaces\n\n- Remove the requirement to add documentation and comments for public interfaces and complex logic.\n\nSigned-off-by: umaru <15875339926@139.com>",
      "date": "2025-09-17T05:45:14Z"
    },
    {
      "message": "feat: \"Introduce Lab app with models and API endpoints\"\n\n- Add a `Lab` app with initialization, admin registration, and configuration (`LabConfig`).\n- Add Django models for managing Lab entities: `LabImage`, `InfraInstance`, and `LabEnv`.\n- Add the initial database migrations for creating tables corresponding to the `LabImage`, `InfraInstance`, and `LabEnv` models, along with model relationships and constraints.\n- Register Django Rest Framework serializers for `LabImage`, `InfraInstance`, and `LabEnv`, including validation logic for fields and properties.\n- Integrate viewsets for `LabImage`, `InfraInstance`, and `LabEnv`, with filtering, searching, and ordering capabilities.\n- Include optional custom actions in the `InfraInstance` and `LabEnv` viewsets for managing instance/environment lifecycle operations such as start, stop, restart, and status retrieval.\n- Add API endpoints via a router for the `Lab` module, covering CRUD operations and specialized actions for the models (`LabImage`, `InfraInstance`, and `LabEnv`).\n- Implement `LabImage` view actions to filter by image type (`IDE` or `Infrastructure`) and list all associated instances.\n- Stub lifecycle actions (start, stop, restart, etc.) serve as placeholders for future backend integration.\n- Add module-level `__init__.py` files to organize models, serializers, services, and views for the `Lab` app.\n\nSigned-off-by: umaru <15875339926@139.com>",
      "date": "2025-09-17T04:11:14Z"
    },
    {
      "message": "feat: improve `ToolsNodes` setup and URL handling logic\n\n- Add `mcp-servers/` to the `.gitignore` file.\n- Introduce `command` and `args` attributes to the `ToolsServer` class with default values.\n- Log the number of `tools_servers` during the `setup` process in `ToolsNodes`.\n- Add detailed logic for handling `stdio-mcp:` URLs in `ToolsNodes` by configuring `command`, `args`, and `transport` as `stdio`.\n\nSigned-off-by: umaru <15875339926@139.com>",
      "date": "2025-09-16T10:15:39Z"
    },
    {
      "message": "refactor: switch to attribute-style access for user messages\n\n- Update access method for `graph_user_message` to use attribute-style instead of dictionary-style indexing.\n\nSigned-off-by: umaru <15875339926@139.com>",
      "date": "2025-09-16T03:44:14Z"
    },
    {
      "message": "refactor: refactor graph_request handling in BasicNode logic\n\n- Add `graph_user_message` as an optional field to `BasicLLMRequest`\n- Update the path to `graph_user_message` in `BasicNode` to access it from `config[\"configurable\"][\"graph_request\"]`\n- Modify `BasicNode` to set `graph_user_message` on the request object instead of updating it directly in the `config` dictionary\n\nSigned-off-by: umaru <15875339926@139.com>",
      "date": "2025-09-16T03:42:13Z"
    },
    {
      "message": "docs: configure sitemap generation for Docusaurus\n\n- Add sitemap configuration to Docusaurus with a weekly change frequency, excluding `/tags/**`, and generating `sitemap.xml`.\n\nSigned-off-by: umaru <15875339926@139.com>",
      "date": "2025-09-15T12:04:47Z"
    },
    {
      "message": "feat: introduce ReAct Agent for structured request handling\n\n- Add detailed requirements for Copilot to carefully understand requests and question unreasonable designs.\n- Replace the base template system with a ReAct Agent template system for a more structured problem-solving methodology.\n- Implement a new `github_tools.py` module to fetch GitHub commit data with validation, error handling, and user grouping based on commits.\n- Introduce pagination support for retrieving GitHub commits efficiently with safety checks.\n- Add a new `ReAct Agent` system prompt template emphasizing reasoning, action steps, security, and safety measures in response handling.\n\nSigned-off-by: umaru <15875339926@139.com>",
      "date": "2025-09-15T08:51:45Z"
    },
    {
      "message": "chore: standardize labels and navigation for improved usability\n\n- Rename the \"PlayGround\" category label to \"Lab\"\n- Update a navigation link from a placeholder `#` to `/docs/deploy/docker-compose`\n- Remove the \"ä¼ä¸šç‰ˆ\" menu item from the config\n- Change the Docusaurus start script to listen on port 3001 instead of the default port\n\nSigned-off-by: umaru <15875339926@139.com>",
      "date": "2025-09-15T07:32:22Z"
    },
    {
      "message": "feat: add models, APIs, and filters for ML prediction features\n\n- Add filters for `log_clustering_*` models with filters like `CharFilter`, `DateTimeFilter`, and `ChoiceFilter`.\n- Add filters for `timeseries_predict_*` models to support filtering on key fields like `status`, `created_by`, and time-based queries.\n- Create models for `log_clustering_*` entities, such as datasets, train data, train jobs, train history, and service. Include fields for metadata, relationships, and train-specific attributes like `algorithm`, `status`, and evaluation metrics.\n- Create models for `timeseries_predict_*` entities, including datasets, train data, train jobs, train history, and service. Add similar metadata and relationships as `log_clustering`.\n- Add Django migrations to create necessary database tables for `log_clustering_*` and `timeseries_predict_*` models, including relationships and properties for clustering and prediction features.\n- Add serializers for `log_clustering_*` and `timeseries_predict_*` models to serialize and manage entities like datasets, train data, train jobs, and services.\n- Add viewsets for `log_clustering_*` entities to manage CRUD and list operations, complete with permissions and filtering.\n- Add viewsets for `timeseries_predict_*` entities with similar capabilities as their log clustering counterparts.\n- Extend `apps/mlops/urls.py` to include endpoints for managing `log_clustering_*` and `timeseries_predict_*` entities.\n\nSigned-off-by: umaru <15875339926@139.com>",
      "date": "2025-09-15T06:24:55Z"
    },
    {
      "message": "refactor: simplify message processing by removing filtering logic\n\n- Simplify the processing of human messages by removing keyword-based filtering logic and directly formatting messages for display.\n- Remove logic for identifying \"internal process\" messages, simplifying their treatment within the system.\n- Delete keyword-based logic for identifying and prioritizing computational content.\n- Remove unnecessary checks for technical message filtering in the `_extract_meaningful_content` function, enabling more straightforward content extraction.\n- Delete the `_is_internal_process_message` and `_is_obvious_technical_message` helper functions, consolidating logic and reducing complexity.\n\nSigned-off-by: umaru <15875339926@139.com>",
      "date": "2025-09-15T02:59:38Z"
    }
  ],
